    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "While discussing the pitfalls of the watch expression implementation, I wonder if we can bypass the watch expression logic and utilize existing conditional Solidity expressions. All those branches (and requires) are interesting places to set a conditional breakpoint. For example, in the snippet below, with the source range w/in a conditional, a user could specify `br (true | false)` where `br true` would break when the underlying expression evaluates to true, and, `br false` breaks when not true.\r\n\r\n```console\r\nMetaCoin.sol:\r\n\r\n19:\r\n20:         function sendCoin(address receiver, uint amount) public returns(bool sufficient) {\r\n21:                 if (balances[msg.sender] < amount) return false;\r\n                                               ^^^^^^\r\n\r\ndebug(development:0x9d8877d0...)> br true <-- break on MetaCoin.sol:21 if `balances[msg.sender] < amount` is true\r\n```\r\n",
